Description: Radiology Protocols is a SaaS-based cloud that provides image-supported radiology protocols and multi-lingual screening forms.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Radiology Protocols is an cloud hosted SaaS that provides image-supported Radiology Protocols, as well as multi-lingual screening forms, a variety of calculators, and pre-screening information. Radiology Protocols is a venture that responds to the huge opportunity that exists in the $120 billion dollar medical imaging industry, which represents 7â€“8% of total healthcare spending in the US. Each year, up to $24 billion dollars in waste can be attributed to repeated MRI and other advanced imaging scans, miscommunication, and other errors  The Radiology Protocols team is tackling the problem of inefficiency and waste in the medical imaging industry by offering a customizable, scalable platform that provides centralized management and storage of imaging protocols among hospitals, medical groups, private practices, and health networks. Instead of manually updating protocols, creating copies, and distributing them to the imaging technicians, protocols can be created or updated on the fly and pushed from the cloud straight to the technicians work space immediately. This centralized management of imaging protocols will ensure technicians follow the appropriate procedures to produce high quality images the first time around, providing radiologists with the critical information they need to correctly diagnose patients and at the same time eliminating waste from rerunning tests to get accurate results. The core features of the Radiology Protocols application include: * Complete Radiology Protocols Library 2.0 for the entire human body that includes detailed instructions for technicians. * Built in contrast drug dosage and unit conversion calculators to ensure correct contrast dosing for optimal test images * Screening form designer & library to keep patients informed and safe during the testing process * Scalable SaaS architecture to meet the needs of various health organizations and providers with advanced enterprise, facility, and organization permissions. * An intuitive Protocol & Image Builder for customizing specifications and creating unique protocol databases tailored to an institutions specific needs. * Currently available in 3 different languages, with more being added in the future.

Description: The T1 Trust is dedicated to rebuilding the historic Pennsylvania Railroad T1 Steam Locomotive
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Pennsylvania Railroad (PRR) T1 Steam Locomotive Trust is a non-profit organization that believes in thinking differently about preservation. Through hard work, dedicated volunteers and the financial support of many generous donors from around the globe, the T1 Trust is constructing PRR T1 5550. Slated to become the fifty-third locomotive of its class when complete, 5550 combines stunning art deco design with a unique 4-4-4-4 wheel arrangement.  The PRR T1 represents the pinnacle of steam locomotive design in the United States. These locomotives had the capability of achieving speeds in excess of 120 mph, and anecdotal reports indicate that speeds of up to 140 mph were attained. In all, 52 class T1 locomotives were produced, 25 at the PRR's Altoona shops and 27 at the Baldwin Locomotive Works in Philadelphia. Sadly, not a single example of this magnificent machine escaped the scrapper's torch. We aim to right that wrong. We value preservation, education and history. The United States has a long and integral history with railroads and specifically, steam locomotives. The production of PRR T1 5550 will fill a large gap in that essential history.
